<br>
The reason is KCoG raids are so different than anything else out there.  You have no control over who will show up, no idea how many or how few people you'll have.  You have no clue about which classes will show.  Everything is so random.  Add to that you probably dont even know 90% of the raiders and they dont know you.<br>
<br>
Herding cats is one of the best descriptions I've heard of leading a KCoG raid.<br>
<br>
Even working under a regular raid leader doesnt prepare you really.  I helped a bit with Talovar on a Fellowship of Faydark run KCoG Fear raid, and then ran a nice little Kael / Siren's Grotto weekend before my first KCoG Hate raid.  Both went well, and both showed me many things.<br>
<br>
Neither prepared me for that first Hate raid.<br>
<br>
Of course, had I not done either it probably would have been worse.  But really nothing you do can prepare you for that first raid.  Its why I expect a new raid leader to fail the first time or two when they take over.  Its no criticism on their part or the part of their raiders.  Its simply that they need to gain experience and there's no way you can do so other than with first hand experience.<br>
<br>
Even mentoring under someone you have that feeling that even if you screw up, they'll take over.  Its not until your tossed out there to sink or swim with the responsibility of keeping 60 people alive that you really understand what your getting into.<br>
<br>
This is NOT to say I wouldnt mind seeing some sort of Apprentice program going on.  Or mentoring or the like.  Having qualified raid leaders who can take over is a very good thing.  I just dont see it as being very practicle.<br>
<br>
If you are interested I'd suggest talking to the current Raid Leaders and see if you cant help out.  Either as a raid second, group maker, loot master, etc.  Learn some ropes.<br>
<br>
I can assure you regardless it wont be an experience that will go to waste.  Once you lead a successful full scale KCoG raid...nothing, and I mean nothing, in EQ will ever seem as stressful.  Not an AoW raid, not anything.  Carry off KCoG leadership and everything else in the game seems much easier by comparison.<br>
